  "text": "We rely on a variant of the compressive autoencoder proposed recently in [CITATION_1] , using convolutional neural networks for the image encoder and image decoder [CITATION_2] . The first two convolutional layers in the image encoder each downsample the input image by a factor 2 and collectively increase the number of channels from 3 to 128. This is followed by three residual blocks, each with 128 filters. Another convolutional layer then downsamples again by a factor 2 and decreases the number of channels to c, where c is a hyperparameter ( [CITATION_3] use 64 and 96 channels). For a w × h-dimensional input image, the output of the image encoder is the w/8 × h/8 × c-dimensional \"bottleneck tensor\".",
